1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper focuses on deploying CNNs on low-power MCUs, which is a common application area for computer vision tasks such as object detection and recognition. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a new model for CNNs that aims to improve accuracy and reduce latency, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper deals with the deployment of AI models on low-power MCUs, which is a relevant topic in the field of AI. 
4. cs.EM (Embedded Systems): The paper focuses on implementing CNNs on off-the-shelf MCUs with limited resources, which is a key area of research in embedded systems. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with optimizing the performance of inferential engines on low-power MCUs, which can be seen as a control problem in systems engineering.
